00:35:12,490 --> 00:35:14,430
Like a mountain?

512
00:35:14,430 --> 00:35:15,469
Why do you say that?

513
00:35:15,470 --> 00:35:19,440
Like a mountain, he's steady,

514
00:35:19,440 --> 00:35:23,360
stubborn, and unshakeable.

515
00:35:27,470 --> 00:35:31,660
Like a mountain, he rejects no dirt or dust.

516
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:37,280
I will not move.

517
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:38,900
Go on drawing.

518
00:35:44,900 --> 00:35:46,279
Why don't you talk?

519
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:48,429
Didn't you ask me not to move?

520
00:35:48,430 --> 00:35:50,330
You can move your lips.

521
00:35:52,940 --> 00:35:55,330
Tell me what was going on?

522
00:35:55,330 --> 00:36:00,089
The Psychological Society approved my application and I went there on short notice for a meeting.

523
00:36:00,089 --> 00:36:03,899
Was that nuisance society more important than me?

524
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:08,799
I called the housekeeper in advance to say I'd be late.

525
00:36:11,100 --> 00:36:12,999
Did you tell me that?

526
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:15,010
Did I say okay?

527
00:36:17,770 --> 00:36:20,490
So didn't I rush here

528
00:36:20,490 --> 00:36:22,620
as soon as the meeting was over?

529
00:36:26,470 --> 00:36:27,739
Come down.

530
00:36:27,739 --> 00:36:29,010
You've finished it so soon?

531
00:36:29,010 --> 00:36:30,570
It's not hard.

532
00:37:06,430 --> 00:37:08,189
Aren't you playing favorites?

533
00:37:08,190 --> 00:37:10,619
Haven't you arranged a childhood sweetheart role for me?

534
00:37:10,619 --> 00:37:12,220
When will it be my turn?

535
00:37:12,220 --> 00:37:13,949
I can't wait.

536
00:37:13,950 --> 00:37:15,860
What's the rush?

537
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:17,870
It's your turn now.

538
00:37:24,940 --> 00:37:27,090
He's an ambitious man.

539
00:37:27,090 --> 00:37:31,200
He has undivided attention and is never distracted.

540
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:33,730
We grew up together.

541
00:37:33,730 --> 00:37:37,949
I don't think there would be someone else

542
00:37:37,950 --> 00:37:40,280
who knows him better than I do.

543
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:47,570
This is supposed to be their first encounter.

544
00:37:51,150 --> 00:37:56,519
Back then I didn't expect there'd be so many stories that had yet to happen.

545
00:38:01,970 --> 00:38:03,220
No, no.

546
00:38:03,220 --> 00:38:05,189
You guys don't know each other yet.

547
00:38:05,190 --> 00:38:08,039
Then have we met before?

548
00:38:08,040 --> 00:38:13,319
As you know, he's a psychological counselor brought in by the girl's family.

549
00:38:13,319 --> 00:38:14,319
What about him?

550
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:16,530
What's his attitude to me?

551
00:38:18,940 --> 00:38:24,260
He… has heard nothing about you.

552
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:26,380
I'm his love rival anyway.

553
00:38:26,380 --> 00:38:28,350
He doesn't even know who I am.

554
00:38:28,350 --> 00:38:32,919
Maybe the man I'm playing has been thinking nothing of you from start to finish.

555
00:38:34,670 --> 00:38:36,900
Didn't you just say you are a good actor?

556
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:38,279
Don't bring in your personal feelings.

557
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:40,409
- Keep it up.
- I can't do that.

558
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:55,900
I said long before now that you are going to make it.

559
00:38:57,100 --> 00:38:59,820
Why do you always have so much faith in me?

560
00:38:59,820 --> 00:39:01,570
Do I have a good eye?

561
00:39:01,570 --> 00:39:02,720
Yes.

562
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:04,620
You have a very good eye.

563
00:39:05,900 --> 00:39:09,820
Will I be cured if I take this?

564
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:13,159
This is the thing the man has been doing with the greatest sense of urgency

565
00:39:13,159 --> 00:39:15,330
for his beloved woman over the past eight years.

566
00:39:15,330 --> 00:39:17,480
But now…

567
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:20,770
There's only one step away from curing her.

568
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:24,729
Maybe he's just afraid there'll be something wrong with the medicine.

569
00:39:24,729 --> 00:39:28,009
When he's doing anything, if he thinks too much and only cares about loss and gain,

570
00:39:28,009 --> 00:39:29,629
he'll only have more to lose.

571
00:39:29,630 --> 00:39:31,119
You are not him after all.

572
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:35,720
For a man like him, no matter how eager he is,

573
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:38,050
he's used to waiting.

574
00:39:41,900 --> 00:39:45,520
So guess what he'll say next?

575
00:39:46,770 --> 00:39:48,940
Not now.

576
00:39:49,570 --> 00:39:51,010
Why?

577
00:39:51,010 --> 00:39:53,360
Now the medicine is still in Phase 2 of clinical trials.

578
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,279
It hasn't got the official approval document yet.

579
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:56,950
Then I'll...

580
